thread.title: New Jersey Governor Gets Push Back From Fellow Democrats on Proposed Taxes

author: Kate King
title: New Jersey Governor Gets Push Back From Fellow Democrats on Proposed Taxes
text:
As New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy gears up to present his first budget proposal Tuesday, some of the governor’s fellow Democratic lawmakers have doubts about how he plans to pay for it.
Mr. Murphy, who took office in January, is expected to increase spending to pay for the progressive policy agenda he proposed on the campaign trail, which includes fully funding the state’s public schools and pension system, overhauling the commuter railroad and making community college free.
